fields.name: Elections to the National Council 2015
fields.description: The 200 members of the National Council are elected by the Swiss electorate for a period of four years. The next elections take place on 18 October 2015.

fields.name: Elections to the Council of States 2015
fields.description: The Council of States has 46 members elected by Swiss voters for a four year term of office according to cantonal rules. Each canton has two seats, with the exception of Obwalden, Nidwalden, Basel-Landschaft, Basel-Stadt, Appenzell-Innerrhoden and Appenzell-Ausserrhoden, which each have one seat.
